  1. How many tickets are in this data set? Which time period do these tickets span? Which years have most data?

Solution

The number of tickets in this dataset is 7656418. The time period that these tickets span is from 01:00 07/02/2015 to 23:58 01/25/2019. The year 2017 has the most data.

addr <- lap_sql %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>% 
  show_query()
## <SQL>
## SELECT COUNT() AS `n`
## FROM `latix`
addr
## # Source:   lazy query [?? x 1]
## # Database: sqlite 3.22.0
## #   [/home/m280data/la_parking/LA_Parking_Citations.sqlite]
##         n
##     <int>
## 1 7656418
tsyear <- lap_sql %>%
  filter(!is.na(Issue_Year), !is.na(Issue_Month), 
         !is.na(Issue_Day), !is.na(Issue_Hour), 
         !is.na(Issue_Minute), !is.na(Issue_Wday)) 

tsyear %>% arrange(desc(Issue_Year), desc(Issue_Month), desc(Issue_Day), 
                 desc(Issue_Hour), desc(Issue_Minute)) %>%
  select(Issue_Year, Issue_Month, Issue_Day, Issue_Hour, Issue_Minute) %>%
  collect() %>%
  slice(c(1, n()))
## # A tibble: 2 x 5
##   Issue_Year Issue_Month Issue_Day Issue_Hour Issue_Minute
##        <int>       <int>     <int>      <int>        <int>
## 1       2019           1        25         23           58
## 2       2015           7         2          1            0
lap_sql %>%
 group_by(Issue_Year) %>%
 count() %>% 
 collect() %>%
 ggplot() + 
 geom_col(aes(x = Issue_Year, y = n))

1. Plot Top 10 Ticket Types by Top 10 Car Make:

library("ggplot2")
lap_sql %>% 
 filter(!is.na(Make), !is.na(Violation_Description)) %>%
 filter(Make %in% c("TOYT", "HOND", "FORD", "NISS", "CHEV", "BMW", "MERZ", 
                    "VOLK", "HYUN", "DODG")) %>%
 filter(Violation_Description %in% c("NO PARK/STREET CLEAN",    "METER EXP.",   
      "RED ZONE",   "PREFERENTIAL PARKING", "DISPLAY OF TABS", "NO PARKING", 
      "DISPLAY OF PLATES", "WHITE ZONE", "PARKED OVER TIME LIMIT", 
      "NO STOP/STANDING"))  %>%        
  ggplot(aes(Make, fill = Violation_Description)) +
  geom_bar(position = "fill") +
  labs(x="Car Make", y="Ticket Type", 
       title="Top 10 Ticket Types by Top 10 Car Makes") + 
   scale_y_continuous(labels=function(x) paste0(100*x,"%"))

2. Plot the Number of Top 10 Ticket Types Per Day:

dat <- lap_sql %>% 
 filter(!is.na(Issue_Day), !is.na(Violation_Description)) %>%
 filter(Violation_Description %in% c("NO PARK/STREET CLEAN",    "METER EXP.",   
      "RED ZONE",   "PREFERENTIAL PARKING", "DISPLAY OF TABS", "NO PARKING", 
      "DISPLAY OF PLATES", "WHITE ZONE", "PARKED OVER TIME LIMIT", 
      "NO STOP/STANDING"))  %>% 
  group_by(Issue_Day, Violation_Description) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>% 
  collect()
dat <- as.data.frame(dat)
dat1 <- spread(dat, key = Violation_Description, value = n)
names(dat1) <- str_replace_all(names(dat1), "/", " ")
names(dat1) <- str_replace_all(names(dat1), " ", "_")
library("ggplot2")
ggplot(dat1, aes(Issue_Day)) + 
geom_line(aes(y = DISPLAY_OF_PLATES, colour = "DISPLAY_OF_PLATES")) + 
geom_line(aes(y = DISPLAY_OF_TABS, colour = "DISPLAY_OF_TABS")) +
geom_line(aes(y = METER_EXP., colour = "METER_EXP.")) +
geom_line(aes(y = NO_PARK_STREET_CLEAN, colour = "NO_PARK/STREET_CLEAN")) +
geom_line(aes(y = NO_PARKING, colour = "NO_PARKING")) +
geom_line(aes(y = NO_STOP_STANDING, colour = "NO_STOP/STANDING")) +
geom_line(aes(y = PARKED_OVER_TIME_LIMIT, colour = "PARKED_OVER_TIME_LIMIT")) +
geom_line(aes(y = PREFERENTIAL_PARKING, colour = "PREFERENTIAL_PARKING")) +
geom_line(aes(y = RED_ZONE, colour = "RED_ZONE")) +
geom_line(aes(y = WHITE_ZONE, colour = "WHITE_ZONE")) +
labs(x="Day of Month", y="Ticket Type", 
     title="Number of Top 10 Ticket Types Per Day") + 
scale_x_discrete(limits=c(1:31)) + 
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=45))
